Done. Both deliverables are written and `transcript.json` validates against `transcript_schema.json`.

**Headline result.** `feature_008` is the implied treatment. It raises `objective_response` from **17.2% to 79.8% (RD = +62.6 pp, OR ≈ 19, p<1e-300) in 31% of the cohort** — patients defined by `feature_013=0 AND feature_015=0 AND feature_021=0 AND feature_027=0`. In the other 69% (any one flag set) the effect collapses to RD ≈ +0.8 pp, OR ≈ 1.06.

**Why this subgroup.** A pairwise treatment-by-feature interaction screen flagged the four binary modifiers (each Bonferroni-significant). The four flags are mutually independent (all phi ≈ 0). Each flag, on its own, fully suppresses the treatment effect — additional flags don't further attenuate it. A shallow CART tree independently rediscovers exactly the same split structure. The apparent modification by continuous `feature_022` (PSA-like) is fully mediated by `feature_013`, and within the favorable subgroup the treatment RD is flat across age, Gleason-like grade, and other continuous labs.
